## The Early Mover Archetype in Practice

The Early Mover tag assigned by the polymarket.tips classification system identifies traders who consistently enter markets before liquidity deepens and pricing stabilizes. This is a qualitatively different approach from momentum trading or mean reversion strategies. Early Movers accept uncertainty in exchange for favorable entry prices. They are often buying when spreads are wide and selling when the rest of the market has caught up to their thesis. For 123987456, this style appears to involve extreme selectivity. Thirteen markets is a remarkably small number for a trader sitting at the top of the profit leaderboard. Most high-volume traders on [Polymarket](https://polymarket.com/?r=POLYTips) touch hundreds of markets, diversifying across political, economic, sports, and entertainment categories. A thirteen-market footprint suggests something closer to a sniper than a market maker. Each position likely represents a concentrated bet on a specific outcome where 123987456 identified a meaningful edge before broader market participants arrived.

